title: The Makers of Canada: Champlain
creator: N. E. Dionne
description: LibriVox recording of The Makers of Canada: Champlain by N. E. Dionne. Read by Cathy Barratt A biography of Samuel de Champlain, French explorer, founder of Quebec, and father of New France. ( Summary by Cathy Barratt ) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B part 1 (117MB) Download M4B part 2 (40MB)
